2026-02-26 | Check If Two Strings Are Isomorphic

	Question
Given s1 and s2,
return true if they are isomorphic,
otherwise return false.

	Approach
1.	We must ensure:
		-	Every character in s1 maps consistently to s2.
		-	The mapping is one-to-one (injective).
2.	Use two arrays of size 26:
		map1[c] → mapped character in s2
		map2[c] → mapped character in s1
3.	Traverse both strings:
		Let c1 = s1[i]
		Let c2 = s2[i]
4.	If:
		map1[c1] not set AND map2[c2] not set
			create mapping
		Else:
			verify existing mapping matches
5.	If conflict found → return false.
6.	Time Complexity:
		O(n)
7.	Space Complexity:
		O(1) (fixed alphabet size)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    bool isIsomorphic(string s1, string s2) {
        if (s1.size() != s2.size())
            return false;

        vector<int> map1(26, -1);
        vector<int> map2(26, -1);

        for (int i = 0; i < s1.size(); i++) {
            int c1 = s1[i] - 'a';
            int c2 = s2[i] - 'a';

            if (map1[c1] == -1 && map2[c2] == -1) {
                map1[c1] = c2;
                map2[c2] = c1;
            } else {
                if (map1[c1] != c2 || map2[c2] != c1)
                    return false;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Isomorphic strings require a one-to-one character mapping.
Using two-directional mapping ensures:
	-	Consistency
	-	No two characters map to the same character.
